jo4neo
Interface TraverserProvider

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultTraverserProvider
public interface TraverserProvider

Used along with neo annotation to create a collection based on nodes selected by a standard neo4j traverser. 

 
 @neo(traverser=MyTraverserProvider.class) public Collection<DomainType> members;
The nodes selected by your traversal are filtered by the generic type so that in the example, only nodes that can be seen as a "DomainType" are included. Changes to this type of object property are never saved or persisted (adding or removing members for example). It is effectively passive and should be used as a way to query your graph.

Author:
Taylor Cowan
